<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Nourish1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Nourish,</orth> vb. 1) intr. to be nutritious, to afford rich food: <cit><quote>--ing dishes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>'tis age that --eth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.341" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 341</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) trans. to feed; in a proper and a figurative sense: <bibl n="shak. son 73.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 73, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.353" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 353</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.222" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 222</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 69</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 60</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.8.21" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 8, 21</bibl>. == to support, to maintain: <cit><quote>whiles I in Ireland n. a mighty band,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.348" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 348</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>